The President spoke with Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany to offer condolences for the loss of German life in the attack in Istanbul. They discussed the European response to the refugee crisis and the upcoming Syria donors conference in London. The President expressed support for the Chancellor's leadership on the refugee crisis and discussed his plan to host a Global Refugees Summit in September. They also committed to working together to help those affected by war. On Ukraine, they underscored their commitment to implement the Minsk agreements and discussed ways to strengthen the economic relationship between Europe and the United States.